    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                <head>No. 532.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Heap</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-02-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 28, 1878</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 136.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                        dispatch No. 259, of the 25th ultimo, describing a visit which you made in
                        December last, on the United States steamer Gettysburg, to various ports on
                        the Tunisian coast, during which you state that the officers and crew of the
                        Gettysburg, as well as yourself, were very hospitably received.</p>
                <p>You are authorized to inform the Bey of Tunis that the President appreciates
                        the attentions which were shown to the officers and crew of the
                        Gettysburg.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp; c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
